I think this is no longer the case
I thought we wanted to spread out the extensions over different files. I suppose the code ended up in this file because `Mathlib.Data.Rat.Order` can't import the required dependencies?

Yes exactly. `Data.Rat.Order` will soon be imported by the definition of `Field` (because of `NNRat`), which is needed to give the `norm_num` support necessary for `positivity`. This makes it straight up impossible to put the extension in `Data.Rat.Order`, and means that the extra import is actually not so extra at all.
